CatDescriptText: Mrs. Jacqueline Terry, housewife, 6 Moultrie St., was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 19, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that cab drivers in general take advantage of other motorists and pedestrians in traffic? As a group, would you call them courteous or discourteous?" answer reads: "They take advantage of people sometimes.  Also, if you are in a destination, they will ride you around.  In one cab company, I would say that all the drivers are discourteous.  The other two companies are all right."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Jacqueline Terry standing with three young children in front of brick street and building with row of storefronts with decorative arch above building entrance
